{"title_page": "Rebellion (2020)", "text_new": "{{short description|2020 Impact Wrestling pay-per-view event}}\n{{Infobox wrestling event\n|name       = Rebellion (2020)\n|image      = \n|caption    = \n|tagline    = <!-- DO NOT PUT ANYTHING HERE WITHOUT A REFERENCE INCLUDED TO A WP:RS -->\n|theme      = \n|promotion  = [[Impact Wrestling]] \n|attendance = [[Behind closed doors (sport)|None]]\n|buyrate    = \n|brand      =\n|date       = April 21, 2020<br>April 28, 2020\n|venue      =Skyway Studios\n|city       =[[Nashville]], [[Tennessee]] \n|lastevent  = [[TNA: There's No Place Like Home]] (postponed)\n|nextevent  = \n|event      = [[Impact Wrestling Rebellion|Rebellion]]\n|lastevent2 = [[Rebellion (2019)|2019]]\n|nextevent2 = \n}}\n'''Rebellion''' is an ongoing 2020 [[professional wrestling]] [[List of Impact Wrestling pay-per-view events|event]] produced by [[Impact Wrestling]] and the second event in the [[Impact Wrestling Rebellion|Rebellion]] chronology. The event was initially slated to air on [[pay-per-view]], but due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], the event was moved to an unannounced location and will be broadcast as a special, two-part, television event for the company's weekly television program, ''[[Impact! (TV series)|Impact!]]'', beginning April 21, 2020, and concluding on April 28, 2020.<ref>[https://impactwrestling.com/impact-rebellion-update/ IMPACT: Rebellion Update News, Press Release, April 13, 2020, By IMPACT Wrestling Staff]</ref>\n\nThe event will be broadcast on [[AXS TV]] in the United States and [[Fight Network]] in Canada, both owned by Impact's parent company, [[Anthem Sports & Entertainment]], as well as the company's international broadcast partners, such as [[Twitch.tv]].\n\n==Production==\n===Background===\nOn January 13, 2020, [[Impact Wrestling]] announced on its [[Twitter]] account that it would be holding a second [[Impact Wrestling Rebellion|Rebellion]] event in April at [[Terminal 5 (venue)|Terminal 5]] in [[New York City|New York, New York]].,<ref>{{cite web |author1=Brie Coder |title=Impact Wrestling \"Rebellion\" PPV Date Announced |url=https://www.wrestlinginc.com/news/2020/01/impact-wrestling-rebellion-pay-per-view-date-announced-665599/ |website=Wrestling Inc. |accessdate=20 February 2020 |date=January 28, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Jeremy Thomas |title=Impact Rebellion 2020 Announced For April |url=https://411mania.com/wrestling/impact-rebellion-2020-announced-for-april/ |website=411Mania |accessdate=20 February 2020 |date=January 12, 2020}}</ref> It was later announced that the event would take place on April 19.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Joseph Currier |title=IMPACT WRESTLING CONFIRMS DATE OF REBELLION PPV |url=https://www.f4wonline.com/tna-news/impact-wrestling-confirms-date-rebellion-ppv-301541 |website=WON/F4W |accessdate=20 February 2020 |date=January 22, 2020}}</ref> Due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], however, the event was rescheduled and taped on a closed set at [[Skyway Studios]] in [[Nashville, Tennessee]] between April 8 and 10. It is airing on [[Broadcast delay|tape delay]] as a two-part special of ''[[Impact! (TV series)|Impact!]]'' on April 21 and 28.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Currier |first1=Joseph |title=Impact Wrestling Rebellion to air as two-part TV event |url=https://www.f4wonline.com/tna-news/impact-wrestling-rebellion-air-two-part-tv-event-308746 |website=WON/F4W - WWE news, Pro Wrestling News, WWE Results, UFC News, UFC results |accessdate=14 April 2020 |language=en |date=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Tessa Blanchard]] had missed the tapings resulting in the scheduled [[Impact World Championship]] match to be canceled.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://whatculture.com/wwe/tessa-blanchard-didnt-travel-to-impact-tapings-world-title-match-at-rebellion-off|title=Tessa Blanchard Didn't Travel To IMPACT Tapings - World Title Match At Rebellion OFF|last=Pollard|first=Andrew|date=2020-04-17|website=WhatCulture.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n\n=== Storylines ===\nThe card will include matches that result from scripted storylines, where wrestlers portray [[Face (professional wrestling)|heroes]], [[Heel (professional wrestling)|villains]], or [[Glossary of professional wrestling terms#Tweener|less distinguishable characters]] to build tension and culminate in a wrestling match or series of matches, with results predetermined by Impact Wrestling writers, while storylines are produced on their weekly television program, ''Impact!''.<ref name=\"HSW\">{{cite web|title=How Pro Wrestling Works|url=http://entertainment.howstuffworks.com/pro-wrestling.htm|last=Grabianowski|first=Ed|work=HowStuffWorks|publisher=[[Discovery Communications]]|accessdate=March 5, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6LDla2zy5?url=http://entertainment.howstuffworks.com/pro-wrestling.htm|archivedate=November 18, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Night 1==\n{{Professional wrestling results table\n|future  = yes\n|results = \n|match1 = [[Tommy Dreamer]], [[Rhyno (wrestler)|Rhyno]] and [[Crazzy Steve]] defeated [[Ohio Versus Everything]] ([[Dave Crist]], [[Jake Crist]], and [[Madman Fulton]])\n|stip1 = [[Six man tag team match]]\n|time1 = \n|match2 = [[The Rascalz]]  ([[Dezmond Xavier|Dez]] and [[Zachary Wentz|Wentz]]) defeated [[Fallah Bahh]] and [[T.J. Perkins|TJP]] and XXXL ([[Ace Romero|Acey Romero]] and Larry D)\n|stip2 = [[Professional wrestling tag team match types#Multiple men teamed matches|Triple threat tag team match]]\n|time2 =\n|match3 = [[Willie Mack (wrestler)|Willie Mack ]] defeated [[Ace Austin]] (c)\n|stip3 = [[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]] for the [[Impact X Division Championship]]\n|time3 =\n|match4 =[[Kylie Rae]] defeated [[Kiera Hogan]]  \n|stip4 = [[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time4 =\n|match5 = [[Ken Shamrock]] defeated [[Sami Callihan]]\n|stip5  = [[Unsanctioned match]]\n|time5 =\n}}\n\n==Night 2==\n{{Professional wrestling results table\n|future  = yes\n|results = \n|match1 = [[Jessicka Havok|Havok]] vs. [[Rosemary (wrestler)|Rosemary]]\n|stip1 = [[Tables, ladders, and chairs match|Full Metal Mayhem]]\n|time1 =\n|match2 = Chris Bey vs. [[Suicide (wrestler)|Suicide]] vs. [[Trey Miguel|Trey]] vs. [[Rohit Raju]]\n|stip2 = [[Four way match]]\n|time2 =\n|match3 = [[Joey Ryan (wrestler)|Joey Ryan]] vs Cousin Jake\n|stip3 = [[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time3 =\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}<br />{{2020 Impact pay-per-view events}}\n{{TNAPPV}}\n\n[[Category:2020 Impact Wrestling pay-per-view events]]\n[[Category:Professional wrestling in New York City]]\n[[Category:2020 in New York City]]\n[[Category:April 2020 events in the United States]]\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.impactwrestling.com Impact Wrestling official website]\n*[https://impactplus.tv/ Impact Plus official website]\n{{2020 Impact pay-per-view events}}\n{{TNAPPV|Lockdown}}\n[[Category:2020 in professional wrestling]]\n[[Category:Scheduled professional wrestling shows]]\n[[Category:Professional wrestling in Ontario]]\n[[Category:2020 in Ontario]]\n[[Category:2020 Impact Plus Monthly Special events]]\n[[Category:Sports events postponed due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2020 Impact Wrestling pay-per-view event}}\n{{Infobox wrestling event\n|name       = Rebellion (2020)\n|image      = \n|caption    = \n|tagline    = <!-- DO NOT PUT ANYTHING HERE WITHOUT A REFERENCE INCLUDED TO A WP:RS -->\n|theme      = \n|promotion  = [[Impact Wrestling]] \n|attendance = [[Behind closed doors (sport)|None]]\n|buyrate    = \n|brand      =\n|date       = April 21, 2020<br>April 28, 2020\n|venue      =Skyway Studios\n|city       =[[Nashville]], [[Tennessee]] \n|lastevent  = [[TNA: There's No Place Like Home]] (postponed)\n|nextevent  = \n|event      = [[Impact Wrestling Rebellion|Rebellion]]\n|lastevent2 = [[Rebellion (2019)|2019]]\n|nextevent2 = \n}}\n'''Rebellion''' is an ongoing 2020 [[professional wrestling]] [[List of Impact Wrestling pay-per-view events|event]] produced by [[Impact Wrestling]] and the second event in the [[Impact Wrestling Rebellion|Rebellion]] chronology. The event was initially slated to air on [[pay-per-view]], but due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], the event was moved to an unannounced location and will be broadcast as a special, two-part, television event for the company's weekly television program, ''[[Impact! (TV series)|Impact!]]'', beginning April 21, 2020, and concluding on April 28, 2020.<ref>[https://impactwrestling.com/impact-rebellion-update/ IMPACT: Rebellion Update News, Press Release, April 13, 2020, By IMPACT Wrestling Staff]</ref>\n\nThe event will be broadcast on [[AXS TV]] in the United States and [[Fight Network]] in Canada, both owned by Impact's parent company, [[Anthem Sports & Entertainment]], as well as the company's international broadcast partners, such as [[Twitch.tv]].\n\n==Production==\n===Background===\nOn January 13, 2020, [[Impact Wrestling]] announced on its [[Twitter]] account that it would be holding a second [[Impact Wrestling Rebellion|Rebellion]] event in April at [[Terminal 5 (venue)|Terminal 5]] in [[New York City|New York, New York]].,<ref>{{cite web |author1=Brie Coder |title=Impact Wrestling \"Rebellion\" PPV Date Announced |url=https://www.wrestlinginc.com/news/2020/01/impact-wrestling-rebellion-pay-per-view-date-announced-665599/ |website=Wrestling Inc. |accessdate=20 February 2020 |date=January 28, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Jeremy Thomas |title=Impact Rebellion 2020 Announced For April |url=https://411mania.com/wrestling/impact-rebellion-2020-announced-for-april/ |website=411Mania |accessdate=20 February 2020 |date=January 12, 2020}}</ref> It was later announced that the event would take place on April 19.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Joseph Currier |title=IMPACT WRESTLING CONFIRMS DATE OF REBELLION PPV |url=https://www.f4wonline.com/tna-news/impact-wrestling-confirms-date-rebellion-ppv-301541 |website=WON/F4W |accessdate=20 February 2020 |date=January 22, 2020}}</ref> Due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], however, the event was rescheduled and taped on a closed set at [[Skyway Studios]] in [[Nashville, Tennessee]] between April 8 and 10. It is airing on [[Broadcast delay|tape delay]] as a two-part special of ''[[Impact! (TV series)|Impact!]]'' on April 21 and 28.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Currier |first1=Joseph |title=Impact Wrestling Rebellion to air as two-part TV event |url=https://www.f4wonline.com/tna-news/impact-wrestling-rebellion-air-two-part-tv-event-308746 |website=WON/F4W - WWE news, Pro Wrestling News, WWE Results, UFC News, UFC results |accessdate=14 April 2020 |language=en |date=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Tessa Blanchard]] had missed the tapings resulting in the scheduled [[Impact World Championship]] match to be canceled.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://whatculture.com/wwe/tessa-blanchard-didnt-travel-to-impact-tapings-world-title-match-at-rebellion-off|title=Tessa Blanchard Didn't Travel To IMPACT Tapings - World Title Match At Rebellion OFF|last=Pollard|first=Andrew|date=2020-04-17|website=WhatCulture.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n\n=== Storylines ===\nThe card will include matches that result from scripted storylines, where wrestlers portray [[Face (professional wrestling)|heroes]], [[Heel (professional wrestling)|villains]], or [[Glossary of professional wrestling terms#Tweener|less distinguishable characters]] to build tension and culminate in a wrestling match or series of matches, with results predetermined by Impact Wrestling writers, while storylines are produced on their weekly television program, ''[[Impact! (TV series)|Impact!]]''.<ref name=\"HSW\">{{cite web|title=How Pro Wrestling Works|url=http://entertainment.howstuffworks.com/pro-wrestling.htm|last=Grabianowski|first=Ed|work=HowStuffWorks|publisher=[[Discovery Communications]]|accessdate=March 5, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6LDla2zy5?url=http://entertainment.howstuffworks.com/pro-wrestling.htm|archivedate=November 18, 2013}}</ref>\n==Night 1==\n{{Professional wrestling results table\n|future  = yes\n|results = \n|match1 = [[Tommy Dreamer]], [[Rhyno (wrestler)|Rhyno]] and [[Crazzy Steve]] defeated [[Ohio Versus Everything]] ([[Dave Crist]], [[Jake Crist]], and [[Madman Fulton]])\n|stip1 = [[Six man tag team match]]\n|time1 = \n|match2 = [[The Rascalz]]  ([[Dezmond Xavier|Dez]] and [[Zachary Wentz|Wentz]]) defeated [[Fallah Bahh]] and [[T.J. Perkins|TJP]] and XXXL ([[Ace Romero|Acey Romero]] and Larry D)\n|stip2 = [[Professional wrestling tag team match types#Multiple men teamed matches|Triple threat tag team match]]\n|time2 =\n|match3 = [[Willie Mack (wrestler)|Willie Mack ]] defeated [[Ace Austin]] (c)\n|stip3 = [[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]] for the [[Impact X Division Championship]]\n|time3 =\n|match4 =[[Kylie Rae]] defeated [[Kiera Hogan]]  \n|stip4 = [[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time4 =\n|match5 = [[Ken Shamrock]] defeated [[Sami Callihan]]\n|stip5  = [[Unsanctioned match]]\n|time5 =\n}}\n\n==Night 2==\n{{Professional wrestling results table\n|future  = yes\n|results = \n|match1 = [[Jessicka Havok|Havok]] vs. [[Rosemary (wrestler)|Rosemary]]\n|stip1 = [[Tables, ladders, and chairs match|Full Metal Mayhem]]\n|time1 =\n|match2 = Chris Bey vs. [[Suicide (wrestler)|Suicide]] vs. [[Trey Miguel|Trey]] vs. [[Rohit Raju]]\n|stip2 = [[Four way match]]\n|time2 =\n|match3 = [[Joey Ryan (wrestler)|Joey Ryan]] vs Cousin Jake\n|stip3 = [[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time3 =\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}<br />{{2020 Impact pay-per-view events}}\n{{TNAPPV}}\n\n[[Category:2020 Impact Wrestling pay-per-view events]]\n[[Category:Professional wrestling in New York City]]\n[[Category:2020 in New York City]]\n[[Category:April 2020 events in the United States]]\n\n