-7316 |oclc=1479302 |doi =10.2307/279044 |jstor =279044}}\n:{{aut|Carlson, John B.}} (1975) \"Lodestone Compass: Chinese or Olmec Primacy? Multidisciplinary Analysis of an Olmec Hematite Artifact from San Lorenzo, Veracruz, Mexico\u201d, ''Science'', New Series, '''189''' (4205) (5 September 1975), pp. 753\u2013760 (753).\n: {{cite book|author=Clark, John E. |authorlink=John E. Clark|year=2001 |chapter=Gulf Lowlands: South Region |title=Archaeology of Ancient Mexico and Central America: an Encyclopedia |editor1=Susan Toby Evans |editor2=David L. Webster |location=New York |publisher=[[Garland Publishing]] |pages=340\u2013344|isbn=0-8153-0887-6 |oclc=45313588}}\n: {{cite book|author=Coe, Michael D. |authorlink=Michael D. Coe |year=1967 |chapter=San Lorenzo and the Olmec Civilization| chapter-url=http://www.doaks.org/publications/doaks_online_publications/olmec.html |chapter-format=[[PDF]] online reproduction |title=Dumbarton Oaks Conference on the Olmec, October 28th and 29th, 1967 |editor=Elizabeth P. Benson |editor-link=Elizabeth P. Benson |publisher=[[Dumbarton Oaks Research Library and Collection]]; Trustees for Harvard University |location=Washington D.C. |pages=41\u201372 |oclc=52523439|accessdate=}}\n: {{cite book |author=Coe, Michael D. |authorlink=Michael D. Coe |year=1968|title=America's First Civilization: Discovering the Olmec|publisher=The Smithsonian Library|location=New York }}\n: {{cite book |author=Coe, Michael D. |authorlink=Michael D. Coe |author2=Rex Koontz |year=2002 |origyear= |title=Mexico: from the Olmecs to the Aztecs |edition=5th edition, revised and enlarged |publisher=[[Thames & Hudson]] |location=London and New York |isbn=0-500-28346-X |oclc=50131575 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/mexicofromolmecs0000coem }}\n: {{cite book |author=Covarrubias, Miguel |authorlink=Miguel Covarrubias |year=1977 |origyear=1946 |chapter=Olmec Art or the Art of La Venta |title=Pre-Columbian Art History: Selected Readings |editor=Alana Cordy-Collins |editor2=Jean Stern |editor-link=Alana Cordy-Collins |translator=Robert Pirazzini |edition=Reprint of original paper |location=Palo Alto, CA |publisher=Peek Publications |pages=1\u201334 |isbn=0-917962-41-9 |oclc=3843930}}\n: {{cite book |author=Covarrubias, Miguel |authorlink=Miguel Covarrubias |year=1957 |title=Indian Art of Mexico and Central America |edition=Color plates and line drawings by the author |location=New York |publisher=[[Alfred A. Knopf]] |oclc=171974}}\n: {{cite book |author=Cyphers, Ann |year=1996 |chapter=2. San Lorenzo Monument 4 \u2013 Colossal Head|title=Olmec Art of Ancient Mexico |editor=Elizabeth P. Benson |editor2=Beatriz de la Fuente |editor-link=Elizabeth P. Benson |edition=To accompany an exhibition at the National Gallery of Art, Washington, 30 June to 20 October 1996 |publisher=[[National Gallery of Art]] |location=Washington D.C. |pages=156|isbn=0-89468-250-4 |oclc=34357584}}\n: {{cite book |author=Cyphers, Ann |year=1999 |chapter=From Stone to Symbols: Olmec Art in Social Context at San Lorenzo Tenochtitl\u00e1n |chapterurl=http://www.doaks.org/Social/social07.pdf |format=[[PDF]] online e-text reproduction |title=Social patterns in pre-classic Mesoamerica: a symposium at Dumbarton Oaks, 9 and 10 October 1993 |editor=David C. Grove |editor2=Rosemary A. Joyce |editor-link=David C. Grove |location=Washington D.C. |publisher=[[Dumbarton Oaks Research Library and Collection]] and Trustees for Harvard University |pages=[https://archive.org/details/socialpatternsin0000unse/page/155 155\u2013181] |isbn=0-88402-252-8 |oclc=39229716 |url-status=dead |url=https://archive.org/details/socialpatternsin0000unse/page/155 }}\n: {{cite book |author=Davies, Nigel |authorlink=Nigel Davies (historian)|year=1982 |title=The Ancient Kingdoms of Mexico |series=Pelican Books series|location=Harmondsworth, England|publisher=[[Penguin Books]] |isbn=0-14-022232-4 |oclc=11212208}}\n: {{cite book |author=Diehl, Richard |authorlink=Richard Diehl |year=2004 |title=The Olmecs: America's First Civilization |url=https://archive.org/details/olmecsamericasfi0000dieh |url-access=registration |series=Ancient peoples and places series|publisher=[[Thames & Hudson]] |location=London |isbn=0-500-02119-8 |oclc=56746987}}\n: {{cite book |author=Filloy Nadal, Laura |year=2001 |chapter=Rubber and Rubber Balls in Mesoamerica |title=The Sport of Life and Death: The Mesoamerican Ballgame |editor=E. Michael Whittington |edition=Published in conjunction with an exhibition of the same name organized by the [[Mint Museum of Art]], Charlotte, NC. |location=New York |publisher=[[Thames & Hudson]] |pages=[https://archive.org/details/sportoflifedeath00emic/page/20 20\u201331] |isbn=0-500-05108-9 |oclc=49029226 |chapter-url=https://archive.org/details/sportoflifedeath00emic/page/20 }}\n: {{cite journal |author=Flannery, Kent V. |authorlink=Kent V. Flannery |author2=Andrew K. Balkansky |author3=Gary M. Feinman |author4=David C. Grove |author4-link=David C. Grove |author5=Joyce Marcus |author5-link=Joyce Marcus |author6=Elsa M. Redmond |author7=Robert G. Reynolds |author8=Robert J. Sharer |author8-link=Robert J. Sharer|author9=Charles S. Spencer|author10=Jason Yaeger | date=August 2005 |title=Implications of new petrographic analysis for the Olmec \"mother culture\" model |journal=[[Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences]] |volume=102 |issue=32 |pages=11219\u201311223|location=Washington, D.C. |publisher=[[United States National Academy of Sciences|National Academy of Sciences]] |doi=10.1073/pnas.0505116102 |pmc=1183595 |issn=0027-8424 |pmid=16061797 |oclc=209632728 |bibcode=2005PNAS..10211219F }}\n: {{cite journal |author=Grove, David C. |authorlink=David Grove | date=September 1976 |title=Olmec Origins and Transpacific Diffusion: Reply to Meggers |journal=[[American Anthropologist]] |series=New Series |format=[[JSTOR]] reproduction |volume=78 |issue=3 |pages=634\u2013637|location=Arlington, VA |publisher=[[American Anthropologic